ass-get-resource\\\\n\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void loadsResourceThroughExplicitClassLoader() throws Exception {\\n        ClassLoader classLoader = ClassPathResourceTest.class.getClassLoader();\\n\\n        ClassPathResource resource = new ClassPathResource(CLASS_LOADER_RESOURCE, classLoader);\\n\\n        assertThat(resource.getPath()).isEqualTo(CLASS_LOADER_RESOURCE);\\n        assertThat(resource.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\\n        assertThat(read(resource)).isEqualTo(\\\"loaded-through-classloader-get-resource\\\\n\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void loadsResourceThroughDefaultClassPathLookup() throws Exception {\\n        ClassPathResource resource = new ClassPathResource(DEFAULT_RESOURCE);\\n\\n        assertThat(resource.getPath()).isEqualTo(DEFAULT_RESOURCE);\\n        assertThat(resource.toString()).isEqualTo(\\\"classpath:\\\" + DEFAULT_RESOURCE);\\n        assertThat(read(resource)).isEqualTo(\\\"loaded-through-default-resource-resolution\\\\n\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void fallsBackToSystemResourceWhenNoClassOrClassLoaderIsAvailable() throws Exception {\\n        ClassPathResource resource = new ClassPathResource(DEFAULT_RESOURCE, ClassPathResourceTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n        ReflectUtil.setFieldValue(resource, \\\"classLoader\\\", null);\\n        ReflectUtil.setFieldValue(resource, \\\"clazz\\\", null);\\n\\n        ReflectUtil.invoke(resource, \\\"initUrl\\\");\\n\\n        assertThat(resource.getClassLoader()).isNull();\\n        assertThat(resource.getUrl()).isEqualTo(ClassLoader.getSystemResource(DEFAULT_RESOURCE));\\n        assertThat(read(resource)).isEqualTo(\\\"loaded-through-default-resource-resolution\\\\n\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static String read(ClassPathResource resource) throws Exception {\\n        try (InputStream stream = resource.getStream()) {\\n            return new String(stream.readAllBytes(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777985446284}}\n80:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"4d206cda\",\"parentId\":\"841db311\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-05T12:50:50.636Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_9XXExyCBWOXR9t2gwicucoeP|fc_0dede874ef8c0b930169f9e7aa14b481a1bbacf64f4b4e1485\",\"toolName\":\"edit\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/cn.hutool/hutool-all/5.8.25/src/test/java/cn_hutool/hutool_all/ClassPathResourceTest.java.\"}],\"details\":{\"diff\":\"    ...\\n 50     }\\n 51 \\n 52     @Test\\n 53     void fallsBackToSystemResourceWhenNoClassOrClassLoaderIsAvailable() throws Exception {\\n-54         ClassPathResource resource = new ClassPathResource(DEFAULT_RESOURCE, ClassPathResourceTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n+54         ClassPathResource resource = new ClassPathResource(\\n+55                 DEFAULT_RESOURCE,\\n+56                 ClassPathResourceTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n 55         ReflectUtil.setFieldValue(resource, \\\"classLoader\\\", null);\\n 56         ReflectUtil.setFieldValue(resource, \\\"clazz\\\", null);\\n 57 \\n 58         ReflectUtil.invoke(resource, \\\"initUrl\\\");\\n    ...\",\"firstChangedLine\":54},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777985450636}}\nFILE=/home/vjovanov/.codex/sessions/2026/06/05/rollout-2026-06-05T17-57-21-019e9880-d97a-7252-9121-08ce2c7a0295.jsonl\n14:{\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-05T15:57:24.953Z\",\"type\":\"response_item\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"function_call_output\",\"call_id\":\"call_CkDrssJBhATKnwLxYcaHBy2H\",\"output\":\"Chunk ID: fb75e8\\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\\nProcess exited with code 0\\nOriginal token count: 2980\\nOutput:\\n# Rhei: RM-001.9 Pointer Screenshot Prompting\\n**States:** milestone-finish\\n\\n## Milestone\\n\\nRoadmap source: §RM-001-research-and-first-prototype.9\\n\\nAdd the `prompt_pointer_screenshot` tuple\\n`⟨pointer/gaze screenshot, instruction, agent_endpoint⟩`\\n§AR-004-command-router-and-lifecycle.1 and the narrow desktop-control facade its\\nscreenshot input needs: pointer state, active-window metadata, bounded\\nscreenshots, and clipboard/paste access. The user triggers a pointer-region\\nscreenshot, dictates an instruction, and the router assembles the\\nimage-plus-instruction `PromptBundle` for the agent sink. Ground the work in\\n§FS-001-voice-clipboard-and-prompt-workflows.3 and\\n§FS-003-upstream-capability-providers.4.\\n\\n## Finish Phase\\n\\nEvery milestone plan uses the shared `milestone-finish` Rhei lifecycle:\\n`pending` -> `completed`. Review, product-management, and commit hygiene are\\nordinary pending tasks in the dependency graph rather than lifecycle states.\\nThe first task updates the milestone plan against the current repository state,\\nexplodes the broad implementation slice into smaller milestone-specific tasks\\nwhen the milestone is reached, and inserts an interface/architecture adjustment\\ntask before each generated implementation task.\\n\\n## Current Repository State\\n\\nThe fixed command catalog already names `prompt_pointer_screenshot`, and the\\ncontract crate already has `ContextItem::PointerScreenshot`,\\n`PointerScreenshotContext`, `TargetSource::{Pointer, Gaze}`, `Capability::{Screenshot,\\nPointer, WindowFocus, Gaze}`, and `ConsentGate::{Screenshot, CameraOrGaze,\\nPromptEgress}`. The CLI diagnostic printer also already knows how to summarize\\npointer screenshot and gaze context items without printing context bodies. Do not\\nre-add command IDs, create provider-defined screenshot commands, or expose\\nscreenshot pixels in public diagnostics. §AR-004-command-router-and-lifecycle.1\\n§AR-006-prompt-bundle-and-context-model.2\\n§AR-010-consent-audit-and-retention.3\\n\\nThe remaining gap is the screenshot context boundary and route execution.\\n`route_support(CommandMode::PromptPointerScreenshot)` is still\\n`NotImplemented`, `VoiceCommandRouter` only starts/stops `voice_paste`,\\n`prompt_voice`, `prompt_selection`, and `prompt_clipboard`, and\\n`RouterProviders` has no screenshot, pointer, active-window, or target-resolution\\nprovider. The existing `PointerScreenshotContext` is also too thin for the\\ncurrent architecture because the milestone needs bounded crop constraints,\\nactive-window/display metadata, a short-lived image artifact reference, and a\\nprovider outcome that can report empty/unavailable capture without falling back\\nto a no-context prompt. §FS-001-voice-clipboard-and-prompt-workflows.3\\n§AR-007-native-backend-protocol.1\\n§AR-009-platform-capability-and-degradation.2\\n\\nPrompt delivery, selected-text prompting, clipboard prompting, mouse binding,\\nconsent, audit, and fake endpoint infrastructure already exist from earlier\\nmilestones. RM-001.9 should reuse the current `PromptSink`, `PromptBundle`,\\ncapture/transcription lifecycle, mouse binding selector path, clipboard\\nprovider, and optional paste/text-insertion contracts rather than rebuilding\\nthem. Clipboard and paste are desktop-control facade operations already owned by\\nthe existing `Clipboard` and `TextInsertion` contracts; this milestone should not\\nwrite the clipboard, paste text, submit text, add process-input dispatch, or\\nbroaden into general desktop automation. §FS-003-upstream-capability-providers.4\\n§AR-012-optional-context-and-control-providers.1\\n§DA-001-compose-replaceable-providers\\n\\nPrivacy is a first-class constraint for this milestone. `prompt_pointer_screenshot`\\nmust derive microphone, local transcription, screenshot capture, pointer target,\\nand prompt-egress requirements before capture, gate screenshot capture separately\\nfrom future camera/gaze capture, keep screenshot crops short-lived by default,\\naudit captured sources, bounds/display/window provenance, prompt destination,\\nretention, and outcome, and keep credentials, provider transport details, raw\\npixels, and context bodies out of diagnostics. Platform support should be honest:\\nthe core route and deterministic fake coverage must work cross-platform, while\\nlocal/native adapters may report unsupported screenshot, pointer, window-focus,\\nor display-server capability with explicit diagnostics. §AR-010-consent-audit-and-retention.1\\n§AR-010-consent-audit-and-retention.2\\n§AR-010-consent-audit-and-retention.4\\n§REQ-001-multi-platform-support.2\\n\\n## Tasks\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-1: Update milestone from current project state\\n**State:** completed\\n\\nRe-read the roadmap item, desktop provider interfaces, prompt bundle model,\\nconsent/audit requirements, specs, architecture, decisions, and git state.\\nUpdate this plan for current screenshot capability, platform support, and\\nprivacy constraints.\\n\\nWhen this milestone is next to execute, replace the broad implementation task\\nbelow with a concrete sequence of smaller tasks sized for one agent session\\neach. For every generated implementation task, add an immediately preceding\\ntask that adjusts the relevant public interfaces, provider contracts,\\narchitecture docs, and grund citations before implementation starts. Preserve\\nthe review, product-management, and commit hygiene task order.\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-2: Adjust screenshot context provider contract\\n**State:** completed\\n**Prior:** Task rm-001-9-1\\n\\nBefore implementing screenshot capture behavior, reconcile the public contract\\nfor a bounded pointer screenshot context. Update the relevant functional specs,\\narchitecture docs, provider contracts, module-boundary docs, code doc-comments,\\nand grund citations so the screenshot provider returns a repo-owned outcome with\\npointer target, bounded crop rectangle, display metadata, active-window metadata\\nwhen available, target source, short-lived image reference, and explicit\\nunavailable/empty reasons. Keep the provider primitive: it must not choose the\\ncommand, send a prompt, capture continuous screen history, or expose raw pixels\\nin diagnostics. §FS-001-voice-clipboard-and-prompt-workflows.3\\n§AR-006-prompt-bundle-and-context-model.2\\n§AR-007-native-backend-protocol.1\\n§AR-010-consent-audit-and-retention.3\\n\\nVerify with `grund check` and\\n`rhei validate plans/milestones/rm-001-9-pointer-screenshot-prompting.rhei.md`.\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-3: Implement screenshot context providers\\n**State:** completed\\n**Prior:** Task rm-001-9-2\\n\\nImplement the provider contract from Task rm-001-9-2 in the smallest shape that\\nthe router can consume. Add the contract trait/outcome types, deterministic fake\\nprovider support, capability reporting for `Screenshot`, `Pointer`, optional\\n`WindowFocus`, and optional `Gaze`, and a local/native adapter that either\\ncaptures through a narrow desktop facade or reports platform-unavailable\\ncapabilities with clear reasons. Add focused tests for bounded crop clamping,\\npointer/display/window provenance, short-lived image references, unavailable\\nscreenshot/pointer/window paths, and diagnostic summaries that omit pixels and\\ncontext bodies.\\n\\nDo not mark `prompt_pointer_screenshot` implemented or deliver prompt bundles in\\nthis task.\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-4: Adjust router, consent, and audit contract\\n**State:** completed\\n**Prior:** Task rm-001-9-3\\n\\nBefore routing the command, update specs, architecture docs, router/provider\\ninterfaces, audit expectations, diagnostics, and grund citations for\\n`prompt_pointer_screenshot` as\\n`⟨pointer/gaze screenshot, instruction, agent_endpoint⟩`. Specify the derived\\ncapability and consent gates, target-source fallback order (future gaze only\\nwhen available and separately gated, pointer otherwise), required-context failure\\nduring `routing`, prompt bundle shape, captured-source audit labels, retention\\nclass, prompt destination detail, and platform capability reasons. Reuse the\\nexisting `PromptSink` and `PromptEgress` contract; do not add clipboard writes,\\npaste, submit, continuous context, or agent-dispatch delivery. §AR-004-command-router-and-lifecycle.1\\n§AR-004-command-router-and-lifecycle.2\\n§AR-009-platform-capability-and-degradation.2\\n§AR-010-consent-audit-and-retention.1\\n\\nVerify with `grund check` and plan validation.\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-5: Implement pointer screenshot prompt dispatch\\n**State:** completed\\n**Prior:** Task rm-001-9-4\\n\\nImplement `prompt_pointer_screenshot` in `VoiceCommandRouter` using the provider\\ncontract from Task rm-001-9-3 and the routing contract from Task rm-001-9-4.\\nReuse the existing capture, transcription, timing, cancellation, prompt audit\\nreservation/update, and `PromptSink` delivery lifecycle; require screenshot and\\npointer capability before capture; require screenshot and prompt-egress consent\\nbefore capture; collect the screenshot context during `routing`; assemble one\\n`PromptBundle` containing exactly the pointer screenshot context and the spoken\\ninstruction transcript; mark route support implemented; and audit microphone,\\nscreenshot, target source, prompt egress, destination, retention, and outcome.\\nAdd focused core tests for success, screenshot consent denial before capture,\\nprompt-egress denial before capture, screenshot capability denial before\\ncapture, provider-unavailable/empty capture failure after transcription with\\naudit where applicable, prompt-sink failure after bundle assembly, cancellation,\\nand chooser/direct binding availability.\\n\\nDo not add native continuous context, OCR parsing, clipboard prompt behavior, or\\nagent-dispatch process input in this task.\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-6: Adjust shell diagnostics and platform acceptance\\n**State:** completed\\n**Prior:** Task rm-001-9-5\\n\\nBefore exposing the route through fake/local shells, update README/help text,\\npublic diagnostics, E2E declarations, architecture docs, platform notes, and\\ngrund citations for screenshot prompting. Specify how fake runs configure a\\ndeterministic screenshot artifact and endpoint, how local/native runs report\\nunsupported screenshot, pointer, window-focus, display-server, or permission\\npaths, which prompt bundle fields are printed, which fields remain redacted, how\\nshort-lived artifact retention is surfaced, and how the existing mouse binding\\npath can trigger `prompt_pointer_screenshot` without the listener or chooser\\ndeciding command semantics. §FS-002-command-selection-and-dispatch.3\\n§AR-006-prompt-bundle-and-context-model.4\\n§AR-009-platform-capability-and-degradation.3\\n§REQ-001-multi-platform-support.2\\n\\nVerify with `grund check` and plan validation.\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-7: Implement shell and fake screenshot coverage\\n**State:** completed\\n**Prior:** Task rm-001-9-6\\n\\nWire `prompt_pointer_screenshot` into the deterministic fake/local harnesses\\naccording to Task rm-001-9-6. Add fake screenshot controls, endpoint delivery\\ndiagnostics, pointer/display/window summaries, image reference and bounds output,\\nredaction checks, binding/chooser coverage, and CLI/E2E tests that prove the\\nroute reaches the configured `PromptSink` through the existing selector/router\\npath. Local shell behavior may report real screenshot or pointer capture as\\nunsupported when no safe adapter exists, but the fake route must prove the\\nproduct behavior, consent gates, audit reference, capability reporting, and\\nprivacy constraints.\\n\\nVerify with focused CLI/local/core tests, `cargo test --workspace`,\\n`grund check`, and plan validation unless a narrower command is justified in the\\ntask report.\\n\\n### Task rm-001-9-8: Review pass 1\\n**State:** completed\\n**Prior:** Task rm-001-9-7\\n\\nReview screenshot bounds, active-window metadata, prompt bundle provenance,\\nconsent/audit handling, platform capability reporting, and tests.\\n\\nWrite the review report to `plans/milestones/runtime/milestones/rm-001-9-8.md` with findings grouped as `finding`, `severity`, `evidence`, `required fix`, and `scope boundary`. If there are no issues, state that explicitly with checked areas and evidence.\\n\"}}\n27:{\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-05T15:57:29.183Z\",\"type\":\"response_item\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"function_call_output\",\"call_id\":\"call_N6s7Nmhud87HFC8mqEo1dZay\",\"output\":\"Chunk ID: 2b16be\\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\\nProcess exited with code 0\\nOriginal token count: 673\\nOutput:\\n## 2. Audit log\\n\\nEvery command that captures audio, reads context, writes the clipboard, delivers\\ntext, or sends a prompt bundle writes an audit entry. The entry records which\\nsources were captured, their provenance, the capability state at the time\\n§AR-009-platform-capability-and-degradation.3, the delivery target or destination\\nendpoint, and the retention class applied. For prompt bundles, the router creates\\nor reserves the audit reference before delivery, stores that same reference in\\n`PromptBundle.audit_ref`, and records prompt-destination detail for the explicit\\nendpoint target §AR-006-prompt-bundle-and-context-model.1. A user can later see\\nexactly why a piece of context was sent; dictation entries cover `voice_paste`\\neven when no bundle or context item exists.\\n§FS-001-voice-clipboard-and-prompt-workflows.1\\n§FS-001-voice-clipboard-and-prompt-workflows.4\\n§REQ-003-meeting-recording-to-implementation-plan.2\\n\\nPrompt entries record `microphone` plus the context sources actually read during\\nrouting, such as `selection_capture` with its method or `clipboard_read` with the\\nclipboard provenance label. They add `prompt_egress` only after a bundle reaches\\nthe prompt sink, including prompt-sink transport failures after `delivering`;\\nrequired-context failures that stop during `routing` do not claim prompt egress.\\nA prior dictation session id is retained when the clipboard value carries\\n`ClipboardProvenance::Dictation { session_id }`; otherwise the audit-visible\\nprovenance is explicitly unknown rather than inferred.\\n§AR-006-prompt-bundle-and-context-model.2\\n\\nPointer screenshot prompt entries record `microphone`, `screenshot`, the\\ncaptured target-source label (`target_source:pointer` or future\\n`target_source:gaze`), the short-lived image artifact id, display id, crop bounds,\\nand whether active-window metadata was present. Successful delivery and\\nprompt-sink transport failure append `prompt_egress` and retain prompt\\ndestination detail for the explicit `agent_endpoint` id/label; routing failures\\nfor empty or unavailable screenshot context record the context failure without\\nclaiming prompt egress. The retention class for pointer screenshot prompt audit\\nentries is `ShortLived` because the screenshot crop is a short-lived artifact.\\n§FS-001-voice-clipboard-and-prompt-workflows.3\\n§AR-004-command-router-and-lifecycle.2\\n\\nAn audit entry records whether the audited command succeeded, was cancelled, or\\nfailed after capture, including the visible reason for cancelled and failed\\noutcomes. A pre-capture capability or consent denial returns diagnostics to the\\ncaller but does not claim that audio was captured. §FS-001-voice-clipboard-and-prompt-workflows.1.3\\n\"}}\n35:{\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-05T15:57:36.612Z\",\"type\":\"response_item\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"function_call_output\",\"call_id\":\"call_yt1rctyeLJdaY3CxAB2M2V82\",\"output\":\"Chunk ID: ccd2b7\\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\\nProcess exited with code 0\\nOriginal token count: 1976\\nOutput:\\n    .join(\\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n}\\n\\nfn help_text(topic: HelpTopic) -> String {\\n    let header = match topic {\\n        HelpTopic::TopLevel => \\\"Miniority first working voice CLI\\\",\\n        HelpTopic::VoicePaste => \\\"Miniority voice-paste\\\",\\n    };\\n    [\\n        header.to_string(),\\n        String::new(),\\n        usage(),\\n        String::new(),\\n        \\\"First working voice path:\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  miniority-cli voice-paste without mouse bindings starts microphone capture through the temporary CLI trigger.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Press Enter to stop capture; type c or cancel then Enter to cancel without delivery.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Delivery settings: --clipboard-only writes only the clipboard; --paste requests focused insertion after the clipboard write.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  The development CLI defaults to paste; --clipboard-only disables focused insertion.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Mouse binding contract: repeat --mouse-binding BUTTON=TARGET,ACTIVATION for mouse-only entries.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Mouse entries use targets direct:<command_id> or chooser and activation push_to_talk, toggle, or cancel.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  BUTTON is a free-form matcher label, not a fixed keyword; the supported set is determined by the packaged native mouse listener, which is not yet present on any platform (native_global_listener: platform_unavailable).\\\".to_string(),\\n        format!(\\\"  Direct command IDs: {}.\\\", direct_command_ids_help()),\\n        \\\"  The local shell executes voice_paste and can select prompt catalog targets through mouse bindings, but agent_endpoint delivery reports unconfigured until a PromptSink adapter is installed.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  --agent-endpoint or MINIORITY_AGENT_ENDPOINT=id[:label] names the endpoint target used in prompt bundle and audit detail; credentials are provider configuration and are never printed.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Mouse bindings merge with default CLI bindings and must validate before any listener starts.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  The shell starts the configured mouse listener before capture and reports listener_adapter, listener_capability, and listener_registration setup lines.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Native mouse listener health is reported with global_shortcut; unavailable hook support and unsupported mouse buttons abort before arming.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Listener-emitted mouse events use the same selector/router fields; unbound events report no matching binding with selected_command none, activation_family mouse, activation_style unknown, and states idle,failed.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Listener-driven chooser and unavailable-command outcomes reuse chooser_surface, chooser_command, selected_command, activation, capability, reason, timing, and audit fields.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Key, CLI, duplicate, malformed, or unknown direct-command mouse bindings are configuration diagnostics.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Configured terminal insertion is opt-in with --terminal-insertion and reports terminal_paste or terminal_synthetic_typing only when available.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  If --terminal-insertion-kind is omitted, the configured helper is treated as terminal-paste.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Without an available insertion helper, diagnostics report the unavailable capability and delivery degrades to clipboard_only.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  miniority-cli fake voice-paste <text> runs the deterministic fake voice-paste smoke path.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  miniority-cli fake trigger-bindings runs configured key/mouse bindings through a deterministic listener adapter.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  fake trigger-bindings uses fake-agent-endpoint by default; --agent-endpoint id[:label] changes the prompt bundle target.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  fake prompt_pointer_screenshot uses short-lived artifact fake-screenshot-1 on fake-display-1 unless --screenshot-image-ref, --screenshot-pointer, --screenshot-display-id, --screenshot-display-bounds, --screenshot-empty, or --window-focus-unavailable changes the deterministic context.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  fake trigger-bindings can set deterministic prompt context with --selection-text, --selection-empty, --selection-unavailable, --clipboard-text, and --clipboard-provenance.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  --capability can force screenshot, pointer, window_focus, or gaze unavailable with permission_denied, unsupported_platform, unsupported_display_server, missing_dependency, or missing_hardware.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  --prompt-sink-fail forces fake agent_endpoint delivery to fail after the bundle reaches the prompt sink.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  --deny-consent <gate> forces deterministic pre-capture denial; use prompt_egress to test prompt agent egress consent.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  fake trigger-bindings chooser runs print chooser_surface and chooser_command availability rows before the chooser result.\\\".to_string(),\\n        String::new(),\\n        \\\"Public diagnostics:\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  selected_command, activation_family, activation_style, final_state, states, reason, capability\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  transcript_text, delivery_mechanism, delivery_detail, delivery_submitted, audit_ref, timing_*\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Prompt endpoint delivery reports delivery_mechanism prompt_endpoint and delivery_submitted false; it does not mean focused insertion, terminal input, direct process input, or submit.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Deterministic fake prompt diagnostics also print prompt_target, prompt_target_label, prompt_instruction_text, prompt_context_count, prompt_context, and prompt_audit_ref.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Pointer screenshot prompt_context prints image_ref, display, target_source, retention short_lived, crop/display bounds, and active-window presence; pixels, target coordinates, active-window titles, credentials, transport details, and context bodies stay redacted.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Provider command lines and native engine JSON are setup details, not product API.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Consent, capability, prompt sink, and required-context failures use the same final_state, states, reason, capability, audit_ref/audit_entries, and timing_* fields as voice_paste.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Local selected-text capture reports selection_capture=unavailable(unsupported_platform) until a native adapter is packaged; local pointer screenshot capabilities report screenshot, pointer, window_focus, and gaze unavailable before capture.\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Target-specific global hook packaging, graphical chooser UI, key-only binding configuration, automatic terminal detection, agent_dispatch process input, wake-word activation, ambient listeners, and submit behavior are out of scope.\\\".to_string(),\\n        String::new(),\\n        \\\"Local provider setup:\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  setup command: make install-local-stt\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  model path can be supplied with --model or MINIORITY_STT_MODEL\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  advanced recorder/STT command overrides are for development adapters only\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  terminal insertion command overrides are configured-machine delivery adapters only\\\".to_string(),\\n        String::new(),\\n        \\\"Environment overrides:\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  MINIORITY_RECORDER, MINIORITY_RECORDER_ARGS, MINIORITY_AUDIO_OUTPUT\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  MINIORITY_STT, MINIORITY_STT_ARGS, MINIORITY_STT_MODEL\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  MINIORITY_VOICE_PASTE_DELIVERY=clipboard-only|paste\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  MINIORITY_AGENT_ENDPOINT=id[:label]\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  MINIORITY_TERMINAL_INSERTION, MINIORITY_TERMINAL_INSERTION_ARGS\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  MINIORITY_TERMINAL_INSERTION_KIND=terminal-paste|terminal-synthetic-typing\\\".to_string(),\\n        String::new(),\\n        \\\"Opt-in real microphone smoke:\\\".to_string(),\\n        \\\"  Set MINIORITY_RUN_REAL_MIC_SMOKE=1, then run the ignored miniority-cli real microphone smoke test.\\\".to_string(),\\n    ]\\n\"}}\n36:{\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-05T15:57:36.612Z\",\"type\":\"response_item\",\"payload\":{\"type\":\"function_call_output\",\"call_id\":\"call_r5XXOln1bzqhWKYOdttpiVOC\",\"output\":\"Chunk ID: ff23b2\\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\\nProcess exited with code 0